<subSubSection pageId="86" pageNumber="87" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,295,320]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Schmidt has stressed the similarity to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bierman)" authorityName="Zelazny" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Bierman" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[754,1036,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pavo">
<emphasis box="[754,910,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Rhotana pavo</emphasis>
(Bierman)
</taxonomicName>
, found in 
<collectingRegion box="[1148,1241,295,319]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
and Borneo. It is not possible to provide an adequate characterisation of this species since the 
<typeStatus box="[1001,1099,332,356]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">holotype</typeStatus>
has missing forewings and no abdomen. It seems to differ from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bierman)" authorityName="Zelazny" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Bierman" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[529,808,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Rhotana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pavo">
<emphasis box="[529,686,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Rhotana pavo</emphasis>
(Bierman)
</taxonomicName>
by its lighter colour (e.g. foretibiae and labium), by the facial carinae being contiguous at their bases, and by the poorly developed lateral carinae of the pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
